LOKOJA – The Kogi State chapter of the Christian Association of Nigeria (CAN) has debunked the alleged endorsement of any aspirant or party for the November 16 governorship election in the state. Powered by RubiQube Ad Network Dr John Ibenu, its chairman, refuted the allegation at the CAN Extra-Ordinary Extended Executive Meeting, held at Chapel of Freedom International, Lokoja, on Monday. He said there were rumours in the social media that CAN in Kogi State had endorsed Gov. Yahaya Bello, seeking re-election on the platform of the All Progressives Congress (APC). Ibenu said that the meeting was a consultative plenary meeting of all the five blocks of CAN to consider few important issues, and made their position known to the public regarding the 2019 governorship election in Kogi State. According to the clergyman, “CAN is a spiritual and religious organisation and not a political organisation. All our members belong to as many political parties of their choice and they are free to do so.